<subSubSection id="C3616545FFDFFF9FFFB8143AFC68FE36" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC436CEFFDFFF9FFFB8143AFC68FE36" blockId="31.[113,1091,266,931]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFFB8143AFF01FEF6" bold="true" box="[113,223,330,354]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
All four species possess a narrow evagination in the posterior edge of the metepimeron, an apomorphy possibly developed to accomodate or support the apical edge of the metafemur.All four species are of the same morphotype but are distinguishable by their coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3616545FFDFFF9FFFB814DAFBEDFC37" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC436CEFFDFFF9FFFB814DAFBEDFC37" blockId="31.[113,1091,266,931]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFFB814DAFF00FE56" bold="true" box="[113,222,426,450]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">Remarks.</emphasis>
As far as I know, this peculiar modification of the metepimeron is developed only in two other 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFF1214BBFE65FE76" box="[219,443,458,482]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFF1214BBFEB8FE76" box="[219,358,459,482]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">Macrosiagon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFE0C14BBFD3EFE76" authority="(Germar, 1824)" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[453,736,458,482]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruenta">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE0C14BBFE05FE76" box="[453,475,459,482]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE2114BBFDE6FE76" box="[488,568,459,482]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">cruenta</emphasis>
(Germar, 1824)
</taxonomicName>
(North and Central America) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFFB8149BFEA8FD96" authority="Pic, 1906" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1906" box="[113,374,490,514]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multinotata">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFFB8149BFF59FD96" box="[113,135,491,514]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFF5D149BFED2FD96" box="[148,268,491,514]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">multinotata</emphasis>
Pic, 1906
</taxonomicName>
(South America). My identification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFCC5149BFC79FD96" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1906" box="[780,935,491,514]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multinotata">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFCC5149BFCFCFD96" box="[780,802,491,514]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFCE6149BFC79FD96" box="[815,935,491,514]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">multinotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on its 
<typeStatus id="54C0886CFFDFFF9FFFB8177BFF40FDB7" box="[113,158,523,547]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">type</typeStatus>
specimen, examined by myself in MNHN. However, in some collections, this species is labeled as 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFF29175BFDD8FDD6" authority="(Gerstaecker, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[224,518,554,578]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gayi">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFF29175BFF28FDD6" box="[224,246,555,578]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFECD175BFEEFFDD6" box="[260,305,555,578]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">gayi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFEF7175AFE21FDD6" author="GERSTAECKER A." box="[318,511,554,578]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" refId="ref28880" refString="GERSTAECKER A. 1855: Rhipiphoridum Coleopterorum familiae dispositio systematica. F. Nicolai, Berolini, 36 pp, 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">Gerstaecker, 1855</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
so these names may be synonymous. The relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFF45173BFF20FDF6" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[140,254,587,610]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruenta">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFF45173BFF7CFDF6" box="[140,162,587,610]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFF67173BFF20FDF6" box="[174,254,587,610]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">cruenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFEE7173BFE19FDF6" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1906" box="[302,455,587,610]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multinotata">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFEE7173BFE9AFDF6" box="[302,324,587,610]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE86173BFE19FDF6" box="[335,455,587,610]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">multinotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFDEC173BFD6BFDF6" authorityName=": BEDEL" authorityYear="1895" box="[549,693,587,610]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFDEC173BFD6BFDF6" box="[549,693,587,610]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is unclear. They are of a similar shape with elytra typical for the 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFDC0171BFD47FD16" authorityName=": BEDEL" authorityYear="1895" box="[521,665,619,642]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFDC0171BFD47FD16" box="[521,665,619,642]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFCAA171BFC0BFD16" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[867,981,619,642]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruenta">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFCAA171BFCA7FD16" box="[867,889,619,642]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFC4C171BFC0BFD16" box="[901,981,619,642]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">cruenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares the same host group with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFE9F17FBFE38FD36" authorityName=": BEDEL" authorityYear="1895" box="[342,486,651,674]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE9F17FBFEB2FD36" box="[342,364,651,674]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFEB117FBFE38FD36" box="[376,486,651,674]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which is the only representative of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFC9617FBFC31FD36" authorityName=": BEDEL" authorityYear="1895" box="[863,1007,651,674]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFC9617FBFC31FD36" box="[863,1007,651,674]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group for which the biology is known). In all cases 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFD5817DBFCFCFD56" authorityName=": BEDEL" authorityYear="1895" box="[657,802,683,706]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFD5817DBFD79FD56" box="[657,679,683,706]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFD7D17DBFCFCFD56" box="[692,802,683,706]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported to develop in the nests of wasps of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFE2217BAFDBFFD76" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[491,609,714,738]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Eumeninae">Eumeninae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFDB917BAFCCBFD76" author="BEQUAERT J." box="[624,789,714,738]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" pagination="1 - 384" refId="ref27848" refString="BEQUAERT J. 1918: A revision of the Vespidae of the Belgian Congo based on the collection of the American Museum Congo Expedition, with a list of Ethiopian diplopterous wasps. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 39: 1 - 384, pls. I - VI." type="journal article" year="1918">BEQUAERT 1918</bibRefCitation>
, 
