<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFF35179AFE5AFC96" author="GRANDI G." box="[252,388,746,770]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" pagination="33 - 64" refId="ref28930" refString="GRANDI G. 1936: Morfologia ed etologia comparate di insetti a regime specializzato. XIX. Macrosiagon ferrugineum flabellatum F. Bollettino dell'Instituto di Entomologia della R. Universita degli Studi di Bologna 9: 33 - 64." type="journal article" year="1936">GRANDI 1936</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFE44179BFDB6FC96" author="HORNE C. &amp; SMITH F." box="[397,616,746,770]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" pagination="161 - 196" refId="ref29060" refString="HORNE C. &amp; SMITH F. 1870: Notes on the habits of some Hymenopterous insects from the North-west Provinces of India. By Charles Horne, Esq., B. C. S., F. Z. S. with an appendix, containing descriptions of some new species of Apidae and Vespidae collected by Mr. Horne: by Frederick Smith, of the British Museum. Illustrated by Plates from Drawings by the Author of the Notes. Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 7: 161 - 196, plates XIX - XXII." type="journal article" year="1870">HORNE &amp; SMITH 1870</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFDB9179BFCDCFC96" author="LONGAIR R. W." box="[624,770,746,770]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" pagination="528 - 557" refId="ref29352" refString="LONGAIR R. W. 2004: Tusked males, male dimorphism and nesting behavior in a subsocial Afrotropical wasp, Synagris cornuta, and weapons and dimorphism in the genus (Hymenoptera: Vespidae: Eumeninae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society 77: 528 - 557." type="journal article" year="2004">LONGAIR 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFCC3179BFC79FC96" author="ROUBAUD E." box="[778,935,746,770]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" pagination="1 - 160" refId="ref30498" refString="ROUBAUD E. 1916: Recherches biologiques sur les guepes solitaires et sociales d'Afrique. La genese de la vie sociale et l'evolution de l'instinct maternel chez les vespides. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, Zoologie, Serie 10 1: 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1916">ROUBAUD 1916</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFC7F179BFF1FFCB6" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruenta">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFC7F179BFF1FFCB6" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">Macrosiagon cruenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also twice reared from eumenid nests (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFD49167AFCCEFCB6" author="GENARO J. A." box="[640,784,778,802]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" pagination="239 - 240" refId="ref28831" refString="GENARO J. A. 1996: Nest parasites (Coleoptera, Diptera, Hymenopteran [sic!]) of some wasps and bees (Vespidae, Sphecidae, Colletidae, Megachilidae, Anthophoridae) in Cuba. Carribbean Journal of Science 32: 239 - 240." type="journal article" year="1996">GENARO 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFCD0167AFC6AFCB6" author="SNELLING R. R." box="[793,948,778,802]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" pagination="87 - 88" refId="ref30782" refString="SNELLING R. R. 1963: A host of Macrosaigon [sic!] cruentum (Genmar) [sic!] in Georgia. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 39: 87 - 88." type="journal article" year="1963">SNELLING 1963</bibRefCitation>
). Some of the other 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFF65165BFE59FCD6" box="[172,391,810,834]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFF65165BFEE9FCD6" box="[172,311,811,834]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">Macrosiagon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in which this evagination is missing are also known to be exclusive parasitoids of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFECC163AFEA3FCF6" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[261,381,842,866]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Eumeninae">Eumeninae</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFE7D163BFCEFFCF6" authority="(BATELKA &amp; HOEHN 2007)" baseAuthorityName="BATELKA &amp; HOEHN" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[436,817,842,866]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE7D163BFE14FCF6" box="[436,458,843,866]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE1E163BFDC3FCF6" box="[471,541,843,866]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">nasuta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEA4B3FFFDFFF9FFDE2163AFCF4FCF6" author="BATELKA J. &amp; HOEHN P." box="[555,810,842,866]" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" pagination="143 - 152" refId="ref27704" refString="BATELKA J. &amp; HOEHN P. 2007: Report on the host-associations of the genus Macrosiagon (Coleoptera: Ripiphoridae) in Sulawesi (Indonesia). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 47: 143 - 152." type="journal article" year="2007">BATELKA &amp; HOEHN 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, therefore the evagination in the posterior edge of metepimeron might be of phylogenetic rather than of ecological origin. It is possible that 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFEE116FBFE45FC36" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[296,411,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruenta">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFEE116FBFEE0FC36" box="[296,318,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE8216FBFE45FC36" box="[331,411,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">cruenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFE0416FBFDB6FC36" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1906" box="[461,616,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multinotata">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE0416FBFE3DFC36" box="[461,483,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFE3916FBFDB6FC36" box="[496,616,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">multinotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D4DFFDFFF9FFCCF16FBFC49FC36" authorityName=": BEDEL" authorityYear="1895" box="[774,919,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="B90FEADCFFDFFF9FFCCF16FBFC49FC36" box="[774,919,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="618">M. ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
